Proposed law provides that, beginning on Jan. 1, 2028, for any plan year during which the
published funding ratio meets or exceeds 1.0, no health insurance issuer subject to proposed
law shall apply a numerical cap to the services.
Proposed law provides that for any plan year during which the published funding ratio is less
than 1.0, a health insurance issuer may apply a numerical cap to the services of no fewer
than the product of the minimum coverage standard times the number of member-months
from the most recent plan year, rounded up to the nearest whole number.
Proposed law requires any numerical cap to be stated in the health insurance plan documents
and to be described using the actual numerical cap and not by reference to a formula.
Effective upon signature of the governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
(Amends R.S. 22:1047(B))
